body:
@61yao can we take a look at ScalarFunctionTransformWrapper class as well.

A lot of those functions are used in the ingestion transformation where the probability of a value being null is quite high.

A lot of OSS users face the issue in that case and have to fill null values in the input stream OR create another derived column.

I still think from a user perspective is cleaner to say

```js
{
  bloom: {
    enabled: false
  }
}
```

Than
```js
{
  bloom: {
    disabled: true
  }
}
```

But I'm open to change that if other people think like @Jackie-Jiang. What I think that is important is to decide that ASAP. Once people start using `enabled` it would be more difficult to change it.

